    "body": "New transaction to an owned account for example would be nice to have notifications of. \n\nIPC seems like a strange choice over a websocket (early versions of Ethereum used websockets I think, I don't know when that disappeared) where you could extend this to being able to have getWork messages pushed to farming miners rather than being polled. It's standard practice for most exchanges and other services to run daemons in virtual machines or completely isolated hardware, which with IPC would need some sort of middleware in there as well to ferry out notifications. \n",
